articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: The European Union is dealing with an increase in legal and illegal arrivals by migrants, prompting some member states to temporarily re-introduce border controls within what is normally a zone of free movement.
articles.title: European countries tighten borders

articles.author: Ethan Wang, Joe Cash
articles.description: China will temporarily exempt citizens of France, Germany, Italy, the Netherlands, Spain and Malaysia from needing visas to visit the world's second-largest economy in a bid to give a boost to post-pandemic tourism.
articles.title: China offers visa-free entry for citizens of France, Germany, Italy

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un inspected photos taken by the country's new spy satellite of "major target regions", including the South Korean capital of Seoul and cities that host U.S. military bases, state media said on Saturday.
articles.title: North Korea's Kim inspects spy satellite photos of 'target regions', US bases

articles.author: Nate Raymond
articles.description: Lawyers for former Binance CEO Changpeng Zhao are urging a U.S. judge to reject the Justice Department's request to bar him from returning to his home in the United Arab Emirates until he is sentenced for violating anti-money laundering requirements.
articles.title: Ex-Binance CEO Zhao urges judge to allow him leave US before sentencing

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Argentina's President-elect Javier Milei said on Friday that the closure of the country's central bank, a signature campaign pledge, was a "non-negotiable matter", according to a statement from his office posted on social media platform X.
articles.title: Argentina's Milei says shutting central bank 'non-negotiable'

articles.author: Saurabh Sharma
articles.description: Efforts to rescue 41 workers trapped in a highway tunnel in the Indian Himalayas for two weeks will be further slowed as rescuers are considering drilling through the last 10 meters of debris manually, an official said on Saturday.
articles.title: Manual drilling likely in last stretch to rescue 41 trapped workers in Indian tunnel

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: A fire tore through a shopping mall in the southern Pakistani city of Karachi, killing at least nine people, officials and local media said on Saturday.
articles.title: At least nine people killed in Pakistan shopping mall fire

articles.author: Bassam Masoud, James Mackenzie
articles.description: Israel has received a list of hostages set to be freed from Gaza on Saturday by Palestinian militant group Hamas, officials said, following the release of 24 hostages during the first day of a planned four-day truce on Friday.
articles.title: Israel receives list of hostages to be released Saturday by Hamas

articles.author: Max Hunder
articles.description: Ukraine's capital suffered what officials said was Russia's largest drone attack of the war on Saturday, leaving five people wounded as the rumble of air defences and explosions woke residents at sunrise.
articles.title: Five wounded in Kyiv by largest drone attack yet on Ukraine, officials say

articles.author: Padraic Halpin, Graham Fahy, Conor Humphries
articles.description: Calm was restored to the streets of central Dublin on Friday night amid a heavy police presence after 34 people were arrested following rioting the previous night that was triggered by the stabbing of three young children in the street.
articles.title: Calm restored to Dublin streets after 34 arrested for riots
